The paper proposes a supervised algorithm for collective classification in crowdsourcing, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The algorithm aims to identify reliable labelers, which involves learning from labeled data and making predictions (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on several crowdsourced datasets, which involves evaluation and experimentation (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the algorithm in human-computer interaction and information retrieval (cs.HC, cs.IR).
